# TDD and Testing

## RED
- Write a failing test first.
- Confirm failure is meaningful before implementation.
- Must not write implementation before RED.

## GREEN
- Pass tests with minimum code only.
- Must not refactor in this phase.

## REFACTOR
- Improve structure without behavior changes.
- Keep all tests green and maintain minimum coverage (`80%`).

## Test Conventions
- Use `pytest`.
- Follow AAA (Arrange, Act, Assert).
- Name tests with `test_` prefix.
